supported commands:
    :a get a random number from the radio
    :b print dysnomia timestamp since device activation
    :c print config file
    :h change device name
    :n generate a private key
    :r print rxCount
    :s[#](+/-) increase or decrease a prime modifier
        supported #s l, g, i, o, q, t, d, H, L
        -- all primes will be autotuned if increase or decrease function causes any equation to lose primality
    :t print txCount
    :x save config file

commands can be chained, 
    :cnnnsl+h ACM999
    - will print config file, then 3 new random private keys, then increase the l prime modifier to match the next lower prime, then set handle to ACM999


